headline: CNN Live Event/Special
subHeadline: New Year's Eve Live with Anderson Cooper and Andy Cohen. Aired 11p-12a ET

utterances.speaker: ANDY COHEN, CNN HOST
utterances.sentences: No. No. Do you -- hey, 50, do you give a damn that there are mysterious drones flying over Jersey and New York?50 CENT, AMERICAN RAPPER AND ACTOR: Yeah. utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I also heard. I read that you DJ'd a set from the top of a mountain in Alaska. Where is the craziest place you've ever done a DJ set?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I am I am in such awe following you on Instagram because you're somewhere different every day. You never ever stop. Do you sleep, dude?

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: I'm going to sleep tomorrow. Yeah. It's been a long weekend. I think it's -- what is this, is it Tuesday? What is it?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Is there one place on your travel bucket list you are super excited --

utterances.speaker: DIPLO

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: I think I climbed Mount Fuji. That was pretty fun. I did it in a couple hours.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Wow. You've been on "Watch What Happens Live" a few times, and we've played a game called, is it wider than Diplo's ass in honor of a picture that you shared of your butt on Instagram. I'm wondering if you think Anderson who --

utterances.speaker: COHEN

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: His ass might be whiter than mine.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Wow. This is the game I didn't --

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: My ass never sees the sun, so it's very white.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. He's very -- he's almost translucent. You know, you shared, earlier that you ran the 2023 LA Marathon while on LSD. How is that possible? What was that like?

utterances.speaker: DIPLO

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: What is the most -- I'm so curious. What's the most conventional place that you've done LSD?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Please, oh my god. Hold on. Hold on. Hold on. Please tell me --

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: But it's like a light trip.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: How do we look to you? As weird as we do in real life or weird?

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: I don't even -- all I see is this this camera. I don't even see you guys. They won't let me look at the screen, so I have no idea what you guys look like.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Oh. So can picture us. You can picture us.

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: Show me that for -- show me that for a minute. Oh, you guys look beautiful. I love your shirt.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Of course, we do. Yes. Of course.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: I mean so you're, like, microdosing?

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: Yeah. Yeah. A little bit. I think I might have macro-dosed earlier today, though.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. Macro -- oh, OK. Was it the LSD spray?

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: No. I got a little dropper, little droplets.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: OK. We should point out actually --(CROSSTALK)

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: All right. All right. Yeah. Well, by the --

utterances.speaker: COHEN

utterances.speaker: COOPER

utterances.sentences: What was your song of the year? DIPLO

utterances.sentences: Listen, given what you do, like, do you -- when you go home from work, like, do you listen to music at home all day, or do you want to be around silence a lot? utterances.sentences: I like to, watch -- listen to brown noise. Like, just kind of, like, textures and read and chill and go in the sauna. I don't know. Whatever. Just to kind of, like, ease my mind.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: -- Anderson has been making so much fun of me because there was this video of me dancing at the Dead show that went viral. But you started to get into Dead & Co. this year at Sphere. What did that -- what was that experience like for you? Oh, God, you guys are playing that again.

utterances.sentences: But let me ask you about that, though, because, I mean, I like going out dancing. I love listening to music. I love dancing in clubs to music. At the Sphere, do you -- I mean, is everybody -- are there -- there's seats, though. Aren't you, like, there are seats?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yes. So I mean, I was --

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: This -- I call them twirlers. Spinners? I don't know. COHEN

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: -- who did -- on your show, who was that that I was with?

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yeah. I mean, he's like -- I loved him.

utterances.speaker: DIPLO
utterances.sentences: And he dresses so good. He dresses so amazing.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Yeah, he does. He is so --

utterances.speaker: COHEN

utterances.speaker: DIPLO

utterances.speaker: COOPER

utterances.speaker: COOPER

utterances.speaker: COHEN

utterances.speaker: COOPER

utterances.speaker: COOPER

utterances.speaker: COOPER

utterances.speaker: JON

utterances.speaker: COHEN

utterances.speaker: COOPER

utterances.speaker: COHEN

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Yeah. It might be -- me too as well.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Hey. What do you think was the song of the summer for 2024? And what about your pick for maybe album of the year?

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Song that is -- I don't know. Well, let me tell -- you tell me yours, and then I'll go off with you guys. You go first.

utterances.speaker: COOPER

utterances.speaker: COHEN

utterances.speaker: JON

utterances.speaker: COHEN

utterances.speaker: JON

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Hey. So you released -- I want to ask you about meditation because, I'm a big fan of a guy named Jon Kabat-Zinn, who's a long time mindfulness meditator in America. He kind of introduced mindfulness a lot and promoted it in America in the 70s. You released a pair of meditation albums this year. What inspired you to get into guided meditation?

utterances.speaker: JON
utterances.sentences: Well, I was going through a lot, when I turned 50, and I was basically saying -- meditating and saying affirmations every day. And around that time, I met my partner, Kabir Sehgal, who I did all the projects with. And we got in the studio, and we just started to work on this. He had an idea to really -- he was like, we should do, you know, record guided meditations.And also, I was like, I really want to do these affirmations because it really helped me. And that's what we did. We just got in. It was just the right time. Life is changing. You know, when you hit 50 or you hit, you know, that part of life, you start to reflect back on life and think about the things you want to change and change your mindset and look at life differently. So all of that's what happened, and that's where I'm at. I have a book coming out of affirmations and manifest -- manifestations. So I'm continuing this process. More stuff coming.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: So here we are 23 minutes until the New Year breaks.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Well, it's actually, like, 40 -- yeah, 38 minutes. But, yes, go ahead.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Oh, 38 minutes. Sorry. I'm a little drunk.

utterances.speaker: COHEN

utterances.speaker: JON

utterances.speaker: JON

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: All right. And I like that we're all doing it together nationwide, worldwide in this moment.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: I like it that you're slurring while you're saying that.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: We're going to let you go. You're in Atlantis.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: We're in Times Square, New York.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: Lil Jon, thank you so much. Happy New Year. I hope it's your best year.

utterances.speaker: COHEN
utterances.sentences: Happy New Year, man. Great to see you. Hope to see you soon.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
utterances.sentences: It is about -- its 3-6 minutes until we ring in the New Year.

utterances.speaker: COOPER
